trans-unit.source: Represents the geometry of a circle or ellipse.
trans-unit.target: Representerer geometri sirkelen eller ellipsen.

trans-unit.source: Use the EllipseGeometry class with a <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Path> element or a <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryDrawing> to draw an ellipse, or with the <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.Clip%2A> property of a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> to define an elliptical clip region.
trans-unit.target: Bruk EllipseGeometry klassen med en <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Path>element eller <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryDrawing>til å tegne et ellipsen eller med den <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.Clip%2A>for en <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>til å definere en elliptisk Klippområde.</xref:System.Windows.UIElement> </xref:System.Windows.UIElement.Clip%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryDrawing> </xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Path>

trans-unit.source: The EllipseGeometry class also has many other uses.
trans-unit.target: Klassen EllipseGeometry har også mange bruker.

trans-unit.source: For more information about EllipseGeometry, see [Geometry Overview](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Du finner mer informasjon om EllipseGeometry [geometri oversikt over](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).

trans-unit.source: EllipseGeometry Compared to Ellipse The <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse> class has a <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Shape.Fill%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Shape.Stroke%2A>, and other rendering properties that EllipseGeometry lacks.
trans-unit.target: EllipseGeometry sammenlignet med ellipsen i <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse>klassen har en <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Shape.Fill%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Shape.Stroke%2A>, og andre gjengivelse egenskaper EllipseGeometry mangler.</xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Shape.Stroke%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Shape.Fill%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse> class is a <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement> and therefore participates in the layout system; it can be used as the content of any element that supports <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> children.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse>klassen er en <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement>og derfor deltar i systemet oppsettet; den kan brukes som innholdet i elementet som støtter <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>barn.</xref:System.Windows.UIElement> </xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement> </xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse>

trans-unit.source: The EllipseGeometry class, on the other hand, simply defines the geometry of an ellipse, and cannot render itself.
trans-unit.target: Klassen EllipseGeometry på den andre siden ganske enkelt definerer geometri av ellipsen, og kan ikke gjengi seg selv.

trans-unit.source: Because of its simplicity, it has a wider range of uses.
trans-unit.target: Det har en rekke bruker på grunn av enkelt.

trans-unit.source: Freezable Features An EllipseGeometry is a type of <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> object and therefore can be frozen to improve performance.
trans-unit.target: Freezable funksjoner en EllipseGeometry er en type <xref:System.Windows.Freezable>objekt, og derfor kan være låst for å forbedre ytelsen.</xref:System.Windows.Freezable>

trans-unit.source: For information about <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> features, such as freezing and cloning, see [Freezable Objects Overview](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: For informasjon om <xref:System.Windows.Freezable>Funksjoner, for eksempel fryse og kloning, se [oversikt over Freezable](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).</xref:System.Windows.Freezable>

trans-unit.source: Gets the area of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.EllipseGeometry"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Henter området til dette <xref href="System.Windows.Media.EllipseGeometry"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Some <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> methods (such as GetArea) produce or use a polygonal approximation of the geometry.
trans-unit.target: Noen <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>metoder (for eksempel GetArea) produsere eller bruke en mangekantede tilnærming av geometri.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>

trans-unit.source: The tolerance factor specifies the maximum distance between points in this polygonal approximation.
trans-unit.target: Toleransen faktorer angir maksimalt antall avstanden mellom punkter i denne mangekantede tilnærming.

trans-unit.source: Smaller tolerance values produce better approximations, but they require more processing than an approximation with a large tolerance factor.
trans-unit.target: Mindre toleransen verdier gir bedre approximations, men de krever mer behandling enn tilnærmet med en stor toleransen faktorer.

trans-unit.source: The maximum bounds on the distance between points in the polygonal approximation of the geometry.
trans-unit.target: Maksimal grensene på avstanden mellom punkter i mangekantede tilnærming av geometri.

trans-unit.source: Smaller values produce more accurate results but cause slower execution.
trans-unit.target: Mindre verdier gir mer nøyaktige resultater, men føre til at langsommere kjøres.

trans-unit.source: If `tolerance` is less than .000001, .000001 is used instead.
trans-unit.target: Hvis `tolerance` er mindre enn.000001.000001 brukes i stedet.

trans-unit.source: One of the enumeration values, <xref href="System.Windows.Media.ToleranceType"></xref> or <xref href="System.Windows.Media.ToleranceType"></xref>, that specifies whether the tolerance factor is an absolute value or relative to the area of this geometry.
trans-unit.target: En av verdiene for enumeration <xref href="System.Windows.Media.ToleranceType"> </xref> eller <xref href="System.Windows.Media.ToleranceType"> </xref>, som angir om toleransen faktorer er en absolutt verdi eller i forhold området i denne geometri.
